reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing scent and feel
reviews.reviewText: This toner really impressed me. I was expecting another typical skincare product that touts all its benefits and makes me feel like I’m failing my skin by not using it and 10 other products….this was not the case. This comes in a sleek box with firm black cardboard insert, with the bottle a dark, deep purple, nearly black. It is gloriously simple with just the brand, the item name on the front, and the saying ‘I am Full of Greatness’ in English and in French on the back. Once opened, there is a removable little plug that makes it much less likely to drip or spill out (as I was about to take a photo of it, I realized I cannot find that little plug =( I wish there were another way to secure that little hole). The toner itself has the best scent I have smelled for a while - just the light hint of sweetness and lychee….incredible! The scent just lingers for a little while and is so wonderful. The feel of the toner is lovely and smooth without crossing the line to oily. I’ve added this to my daily regimen and will update as needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Doesn't irritate skin!
reviews.reviewText: I have skin that will randomly flare up with new products but I am happy to report that it did not react to this toner. The presentation of the product is pretty - Love the bottle!! It does smell nice too.I have used this 4 times now and I haven't noticed anything different with my skin - honestly not sure what toner does - maybe smooths out skin? I guess I need to use it longer to see if it makes a bigger difference. What I can say is it did not dry my skin out or cause any reaction - I would call that a win! $25 for the bottle seems kind of average, plus being made by a "celebrity" probably adds to the cost.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This toner has a really nice presentation, heavy glass bottle that is a pretty shade of purple with minimal lettering and a positive affirmation on the side.I'm not a regular toner user so hard for me to compare to others. It was easy to dispense onto a cotton pad. It smelled maybe faintly of aloe, but no other obvious scent. It felt nice on my skin and my skin felt refreshed after using it. It did not cause any irritation or exacerbate my skin issues.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars it's an alright toner, but i think you're paying for the name.
reviews.reviewText: when it comes to brands that are 'created by' celebrities, i am always a bit weary of trusting them, and the price tag attached. this toner isn't overly expensive or anything, but seeing as it comes from Elf beauty, I suspect that the price is heightened because of the celebrity named attached. Elf beauty puts out quality product, but their products are much more affordable than this. it's a pretty decent toner with a light scent to it, but it's not anything super special in my opinion.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Immediate hydration, great scent, and premium packaging
reviews.reviewText: Can we talk about how gorgeous this bottle of essence is? The bottle is so gorgeous! The color, and the weight of the bottle is simply luxurious. I'm also very impressed with the toning essence. It is aptly titled "tranquil" as it immediately calms and hydrates my skin after washing. A little goes a long way, just a few drops is enough, so I know this bottle will last a long time.The essence has a light rose scent that doesn't linger. I am happy to add this essence to my skincare routine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Somewhat quizzical product
reviews.reviewText: On the box it touts the fact that it's unscented, but also brags about being scented. So I get the distinct impression that the creators of this product weren't really doing much in terms of quality control or focus on detail. It also tells you to repeat your daily affirmation while using it, but didn't give me any details as to what that might be.It's a lotion. It feels hydrating. Works alright.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This toner didn't irritate my sensitive skin patches (yay!) and comes in a sleek, pretty dark purple glass bottle that has a positive message on it. Smells great without being an overpowering scent, leaves my skin feeling in a great state to follow up with a serum and moisturizer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Hydrating is incredibly mild to non-existent; tacky/gritty feel after application
reviews.reviewText: Keys Soulcare Tranquil Essence is packaged impressively with a sleek bottle design. It just looks and feels as if it should be luxurious. Unfortunately, its contents did not live up to that luxury. I am not a fan of the fragrance, which I found to be unpleasant and to the point of being a tad overpowering. As such, I used a very minimal amount to test out during its first application . . . and I was decidedly underwhelmed. It did a whole lot of nothing, except leave behind a scent that my pup seemed intent on trying to clean off me. With subsequent applications, I used considerably more, which seemed to have a mild hydrating effect but not by much. Additionally, it left behind a tacky, almost gritty texture to the skin. The overall effectiveness of Keys Soulcare Tranquil Essence facial toner is questionable. I will look elsewhere for my facial toner needs.
